  "description": [
    "Vol 4 No 13 Corydon Cullings Rev Perry preached an excellent sermon on Sunday Mrs Lydia Alexander has return ed from a pleasant trip to Louisville Ky Robert Rochester went to Louis ville Ky on business last Friday The chorus of 30 voices under the management of Mrs Brewer assisted by Prof W Fouse rendered excellent music Sunday evening Mr William Perry is well pleas ed with his school at Cedar Wood To morrow is our rally day good results are expected Rev Wiley of the M E church promised to preach at 3 p m a special program at night the choir will furnish excellent music for the occasion Master Brantis Noyes a a mem ber of the chorus has accepted the agency of The Recorder at this point Let us haye not less than 100 subscribers at once The Recorder is a good paper Notice Crawfordsville Ind Dear auxiliary president nothing pieventing I will leave home for Philadelphia Sunday November the 6th to attend the Parent Mite Missionary Society which convenes the 8 9 and 10 I will guard all interest pretaining to Indiana closely and endeavor to reflect credit on the many noble woman I go to"
